#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:1
msgid "Install from Scratch"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:3
msgid ""
"These instructions are written for Ubuntu 20.04 / Ubuntu 22.04. They are "
"particularly useful when you'd like to setup a Lemmy container (e.g. LXC on "
"Proxmox) and cannot use Docker."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:5
msgid ""
"Lemmy is built from source in this guide, so this may take a while, "
"especially on slow devices. For example, Lemmy v0.18.5 takes around 7 "
"minutes to build on a quad core VPS."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:7
msgid ""
"Installing and configuring Lemmy using this guide takes about 60-90 minutes. "
"You might need to make yourself a fresh cup of coffee before you start."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:9
msgid "Installation"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:11
msgid "Database"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:13
msgid ""
"For Ubuntu 20.04 the shipped PostgreSQL version is 12 which is not supported "
"by Lemmy. So let's set up a newer one. The most recent stable version of "
"PostgreSQL is 16 at the time of writing this guide."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:16 src/administration/from_scratch.md:212
#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:289
msgid "Install dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:18
msgid ""
"```\n"
"sudo apt install -y wget ca-certificates pkg-config\n"
"wget --quiet -O - https://www.postgresql.org/media/keys/ACCC4CF8.asc | sudo "
"apt-key add -\n"
"sudo sh -c 'echo \"deb http://apt.postgresql.org/pub/repos/apt/ "
"$(lsb_release -cs)-pgdg main\" >> /etc/apt/sources.list.d/pgdg.list'\n"
"sudo apt update\n"
"sudo apt install libssl-dev libpq-dev postgresql\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:26
msgid "Setup Lemmy database"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:28
msgid ""
"Replace db-passwd with a unique password of your choice in the commands "
"below."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:30
msgid ""
"```\n"
"sudo -iu postgres psql -c \"CREATE USER lemmy WITH PASSWORD 'db-passwd';\"\n"
"sudo -iu postgres psql -c \"CREATE DATABASE lemmy WITH OWNER lemmy;\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:35
msgid ""
"If you're migrating from an older version of Lemmy, the following might be "
"required."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:37
msgid ""
"```\n"
"sudo -iu postgres psql -c \"ALTER USER lemmy WITH SUPERUSER;\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:41
msgid ""
"Tune your PostgreSQL settings to match your hardware via [this guide]"
"(https://pgtune.leopard.in.ua/#/)"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:43
msgid "Setup md5 auth"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:45
msgid ""
"Your Postgres config might need to be edited to allow password "
"authentication instead of peer authentication. Simply add the following to "
"your `pg_hba.conf`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:51
msgid "Install Rust"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:53
msgid ""
"For the Rust compiles, it is ideal to use a non-privileged Linux account on "
"your system. Install Rust by following the instructions on [Rustup](https://"
"rustup.rs/) (using a non-privileged Linux account, it will install file in "
"that user's home folder for rustup and cargo)."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:55
msgid ""
"protobuf-compiler may be required for Ubuntu 20.04 or 22.04 installs, please "
"report testing in lemmy-docs issues."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:61
msgid "Setup pict-rs (Optional)"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:63
msgid ""
"You can skip this section if you don't require image hosting, but **NOTE "
"that Lemmy-ui will still allow users to attempt uploading images even if "
"pict-rs is not configured. In this situation, the upload will fail and users "
"will receive technical error messages.**"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:65
msgid ""
"Lemmy supports image hosting using [pict-rs](https://git.asonix.dog/asonix/"
"pict-rs/). We need to install a couple of dependencies for this. It requires "
"the `magick` command which comes with Imagemagick version 7, but Ubuntu "
"20.04 only comes with Imagemagick 6. So you need to install that command "
"manually, eg from the [official website](https://imagemagick.org/script/"
"download.php#linux)."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:67
msgid ""
"**NOTE: on standard LXC containers an AppImage-based ImageMagick "
"installation [will not work properly](https://github.com/LemmyNet/lemmy/"
"issues/4112). It uses FUSE which will emit \"permission denied\" errors when "
"trying to upload an image through pict-rs. You must use alternative "
"installation methods, such as [imei.sh](https://github.com/SoftCreatR/imei)."
"**"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:69
msgid "AppImage-based installation of ImageMagick"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:71
msgid ""
"```\n"
"sudo apt install ffmpeg exiftool libgexiv2-dev --no-install-recommends\n"
"# save the file to a working folder it can be verified before copying to /"
"usr/bin/\n"
"wget https://download.imagemagick.org/ImageMagick/download/binaries/magick\n"
"# compare hash with the \"message digest\" on the official page linked "
"above\n"
"sha256sum magick\n"
"sudo mv magick /usr/bin/\n"
"sudo chmod 755 /usr/bin/magick\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:81
msgid "imei.sh-based installation of ImageMagick"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:83
msgid ""
"Follow the instructions from the [official imei.sh page on GitHub](https://"
"github.com/SoftCreatR/imei)"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:85
msgid "Standalone pict-rs installation"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:87
msgid ""
"Since we're building stuff from source here, let's do the same for pict-rs. "
"Follow the [instructions here](https://git.asonix.dog/asonix/pict-rs/#user-"
"content-compile-from-source)."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:89
msgid "Lemmy Backend"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:91
msgid "Build the backend"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:93
msgid "Create user account on Linux for the lemmy_server application"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:99
msgid ""
"Compile and install Lemmy, given the from-scratch intention, this will be "
"done via GitHub checkout. This can be done by a normal unprivledged user "
"(using the same Linux account you used for rustup)."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:109
msgid "Then build Lemmy with the following command:"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:115
msgid "Deployment"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:117
msgid ""
"Because we should [follow the Linux way](https://tldp.org/LDP/Linux-"
"Filesystem-Hierarchy/html/opt.html), we should use the `/opt` directory to "
"colocate the backend, frontend and pict-rs."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:129
msgid ""
"Note that it might not be the most obvious thing, but **creating the pictrs "
"directories is not optional**."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:131
msgid "Then copy the binary."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:137
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:139
msgid ""
"This is the minimal Lemmy config, put this in `/opt/lemmy/lemmy-server/lemmy."
"hjson` (see [here](https://github.com/LemmyNet/lemmy/blob/main/config/"
"defaults.hjson) for more config options)."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:141
msgid ""
"```hjson\n"
"{\n"
"  database: {\n"
"    # put your db-passwd from above\n"
"    password: \"db-passwd\"\n"
"  }\n"
"  # replace with your domain\n"
"  hostname: example.com\n"
"  bind: \"127.0.0.1\"\n"
"  federation: {\n"
"    enabled: true\n"
"  }\n"
"  # remove this block if you don't require image hosting\n"
"  pictrs: {\n"
"    url: \"http://localhost:8080/\"\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:160
msgid "Set the correct owner"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:166
msgid "Server daemon"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:168
msgid ""
"Add a systemd unit file, so that Lemmy automatically starts and stops, logs "
"are handled via journalctl etc. Put this file into /etc/systemd/system/lemmy."
"service."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:170
msgid ""
"```\n"
"[Unit]\n"
"Description=Lemmy Server\n"
"After=network.target\n"
"\n"
"[Service]\n"
"User=lemmy\n"
"ExecStart=/opt/lemmy/lemmy-server/lemmy_server\n"
"Environment=LEMMY_CONFIG_LOCATION=/opt/lemmy/lemmy-server/lemmy.hjson\n"
"Environment=PICTRS_ADDR=127.0.0.1:8080\n"
"Environment=RUST_LOG=\"info\"\n"
"Restart=on-failure\n"
"WorkingDirectory=/opt/lemmy\n"
"\n"
"# Hardening\n"
"ProtectSystem=yes\n"
"PrivateTmp=true\n"
"MemoryDenyWriteExecute=true\n"
"NoNewPrivileges=true\n"
"\n"
"[Install]\n"
"WantedBy=multi-user.target\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:194
msgid ""
"If you need debug output in the logs, change the RUST_LOG line in the file "
"above to"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:196
msgid ""
"```\n"
"Environment=RUST_LOG=\"debug,lemmy_server=debug,lemmy_api=debug,"
"lemmy_api_common=debug,lemmy_api_crud=debug,lemmy_apub=debug,"
"lemmy_db_schema=debug,lemmy_db_views=debug,lemmy_db_views_actor=debug,"
"lemmy_db_views_moderator=debug,lemmy_routes=debug,lemmy_utils=debug,"
"lemmy_websocket=debug\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:200
msgid "Then run"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:208
msgid ""
"If you did everything right, the Lemmy logs from `sudo journalctl -u lemmy` "
"should show \"Starting http server at 127.0.0.1:8536\". You can also run "
"`curl localhost:8536/api/v3/site` which should give a successful response, "
"looking like `{\"site_view\":null,\"admins\":[],\"banned\":[],\"online\":0,"
"\"version\":\"unknown version\",\"my_user\":null,\"federated_instances\":"
"null}`. For pict-rs, run `curl 127.0.0.1:8080` and ensure that it outputs "
"nothing (particularly no errors)."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:210
msgid "Lemmy Front-end (lemmy-ui)"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:214
msgid ""
"Nodejs in Ubuntu 20.04 / Ubuntu 22.04 repos are too old, so let's install "
"Node 20."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:216
msgid ""
"```\n"
"# nodejs\n"
"sudo apt install -y ca-certificates curl gnupg\n"
"sudo mkdir -p /etc/apt/keyrings\n"
"curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/gpgkey/nodesource-repo.gpg.key | sudo "
"gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/nodesource.gpg\n"
"echo \"deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/nodesource.gpg] https://deb."
"nodesource.com/node_20.x nodistro main\" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/"
"nodesource.list\n"
"\n"
"sudo apt update\n"
"sudo apt install nodejs\n"
"\n"
"# pnpm\n"
"npm i -g pnpm\n"
"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:231
msgid "Build the front-end"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:233
msgid ""
"Clone the git repo, checkout the version you want (0.18.5 in this case), and "
"compile it."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:235
msgid ""
"```\n"
"# dont compile as admin\n"
"cd /opt/lemmy\n"
"sudo -u lemmy bash\n"
"git clone https://github.com/LemmyNet/lemmy-ui.git --recursive\n"
"cd lemmy-ui\n"
"git checkout 0.18.5 # replace with the version you want to install\n"
"pnpm i\n"
"pnpm build:prod\n"
"exit\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:247
msgid "UI daemon"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:249
msgid ""
"Add another systemd unit file, this time for lemmy-ui. You need to replace "
"`example.com` with your actual domain. Put the file in `/etc/systemd/system/"
"lemmy-ui.service`"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:275
msgid ""
"More UI-related variables can be [found here](https://github.com/LemmyNet/"
"lemmy-ui#configuration)."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:277
msgid "Then run."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:285
msgid ""
"If everything went right, the command `curl -I localhost:1234` should show "
"`200 OK` at the top."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:287
msgid "Configure reverse proxy and TLS"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:295
msgid "Request Let's Encrypt TLS certificate (just follow the instructions)"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:301
msgid ""
"Let's Encrypt certificates should be renewed automatically, so add the line "
"below to your crontab, by running `sudo crontab -e`. Replace `example.com` "
"with your actual domain."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:307
msgid ""
"Finally, add the Nginx virtual host config file. Copy paste the file below "
"to `/etc/nginx/sites-enabled/lemmy.conf`"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/from_scratch.md:309
msgid ""
"```\n"
"limit_req_zone $binary_remote_addr zone={{domain}}_ratelimit:10m rate=1r/s;\n"
"\n"
"server {\n"
"    listen 80;\n"
"    listen [::]:80;\n"
"    server_name {{domain}};\n"
"    location /.well-known/acme-challenge/ {\n"
"        root /var/www/certbot;\n"
"    }\n"
"    location / {\n"
"        return 301 https://$host$request_uri;\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"server {\n"
"    listen 443 ssl http2;\n"
"    listen [::]:443 ssl http2;\n"
"    server_name {{domain}};\n"
"\n"
"    ssl_certificate /etc/letsencrypt/live/{{domain}}/fullchain.pem;\n"
"    ssl_certificate_key /etc/letsencrypt/live/{{domain}}/privkey.pem;\n"
"\n"
"    # Various TLS hardening settings\n"
"    # https://raymii.org/s/tutorials/Strong_SSL_Security_On_nginx.html\n"
"    ssl_protocols TLSv1.2 TLSv1.3;\n"
"    ssl_prefer_server_ciphers on;\n"
"    ssl_ciphers 'ECDHE-ECDSA-AES256-GCM-SHA384:ECDHE-RSA-AES256-GCM-SHA384:"
"ECDHE-ECDSA-CHACHA20-POLY1305:ECDHE-RSA-CHACHA20-POLY1305:ECDHE-ECDSA-AES128-"
"GCM-SHA256:ECDHE-RSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256:ECDHE-ECDSA-AES256-SHA384:ECDHE-RSA-"
"AES256-SHA384:ECDHE-ECDSA-AES128-SHA256:ECDHE-RSA-AES128-SHA256';\n"
"    ssl_session_timeout  10m;\n"
"    ssl_session_cache shared:SSL:10m;\n"
"    ssl_session_tickets on;\n"
"    ssl_stapling on;\n"
"    ssl_stapling_verify on;\n"
"\n"
"    # Hide nginx version\n"
"    server_tokens off;\n"
"\n"
"    # Enable compression for JS/CSS/HTML bundle, for improved client load "
"times.\n"
"    # It might be nice to compress JSON, but leaving that out to protect "
"against potential\n"
"    # compression+encryption information leak attacks like BREACH.\n"
"    gzip on;\n"
"    gzip_types text/css application/javascript image/svg+xml;\n"
"    gzip_vary on;\n"
"\n"
"    # Only connect to this site via HTTPS for the two years\n"
"    add_header Strict-Transport-Security \"max-age=63072000\";\n"
"\n"
"    # Various content security headers\n"
"    add_header Referrer-Policy \"same-origin\";\n"
"    add_header X-Content-Type-Options \"nosniff\";\n"
"    add_header X-Frame-Options \"DENY\";\n"
"    add_header X-XSS-Protection \"1; mode=block\";\n"
"\n"
"    # Upload limit for pictrs\n"
"    client_max_body_size 20M;\n"
"\n"
"    # frontend\n"
"    location / {\n"
"      # The default ports:\n"
"\n"
"      set $proxpass \"http://0.0.0.0:1234\";\n"
"      if ($http_accept ~ \"^application/.*$\") {\n"
"        set $proxpass \"http://0.0.0.0:8536\";\n"
"      }\n"
"      if ($request_method = POST) {\n"
"        set $proxpass \"http://0.0.0.0:8536\";\n"
"      }\n"
"      proxy_pass $proxpass;\n"
"\n"
"      rewrite ^(.+)/+$ $1 permanent;\n"
"\n"
"      # Send actual client IP upstream\n"
"      proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;\n"
"      proxy_set_header Host $host;\n"
"      proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;\n"
"    }\n"
"\n"
"    # backend\n"
"    location ~ ^/(api|pictrs|feeds|nodeinfo|.well-known) {\n"
"      proxy_pass http://0.0.0.0:8536;\n"
"      proxy_http_version 1.1;\n"
"      proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;\n"
"      proxy_set_header Connection \"upgrade\";\n"
"\n"
"      # Rate limit\n"
"      limit_req zone={{domain}}_ratelimit burst=30 nodelay;\n"
"\n"
"      # Add IP forwarding headers\n"
"      proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;\n"
"      proxy_set_header Host $host;\n"
"      proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"access_log /var/log/nginx/access.log combined;\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

